<br>
There are 3 spawn spots in CS.  One is near SG entrance.  About 4 spawns here, and I don't think they can be pulled solo since they seems pretty close to eahc other.  Another spawn spot is directly below tower near Bulthors.  3 spaws within aggro range of each other, and apparently 2 in the water, although I only saw one.  The one I saw under water appeared far enough away to pull solo, as I pulled it twice and never got aggroed and saw nothing near it.  Problem with this camp is hard to pull solos, and if you get charmed, you get charmed into 3 or 4 sirens, and possibly several ulthork.  There's a lesser known siren spot directly behind this ledge on the other side of the cliff.  Underwater is a sunken ship, and there is a rock near it with 2 sirens spawns, close enough to aggro if one is pulled.  On the cliff wall there is a rock with 1 siren pull.  Stick with this one. <br>
<br>
You can sit on the rock wall a ways away in range to cast, but not in range to aggro this siren, in case you don't like fighting underwater.  This makes things easier. With enticers, I can kill them on the rock without ever going under water.<br>
<br>
Now, for how to kill them.  I had 130 MR when I tried.  I'd suggest very high MR, and steelskin.  All their spells are MR based, including nukes.  I think I maybe completely resisted 3 or 4 nukes from enticers.  Even when green, their nukes hit hard, for around 150.  For enticers, lead with IC, then cast Tishan's discord to interupt the stun that will push you backward into water. Immediately after the stun, follow up with draught, which usually starts them running, then finish with shock of lightning.  Very easy and I could usually take these without taking dmg, although on several occasions they almost got me.  If the siren runs off the rock after your initial IC, drop into water, wait a few seconds to stop moving, then cast either root or stun, and then draught. Root isn't real important on these since you can kill them quickly.  All other sirens need to be rooted because if they hit you under wate,r you'll move back and won't be able to cast until you come to a complete stop.<br>
<br>
If the two sirens on the underwater rock were both enticers, I could usually cast on one just in range, without aggroing the other.  Same as if I cast on a seductress or enchanter first. the other was low enough not to aggro.  Always cast on the higher one first.  I never tried a seductress and an enchanter, or 2 sedcutri, or anything other than an enticer and something higher. If I ever ran into this I would leave. <br>
<br>
For Seductress, I would IC, stun, IC again, root, then driaght, then stun, then IC if necessary, Usually after you stun them you have enough time to get off a second IC before they cast, although it's close.  They cast fast.  Would probably have been better for me to have tishan's and marklar's up at same time for double stuns.  I would not recommend doing these or enchantress with below 130 MR.  Even with that, you will get charmed and nuked to hell.  I was charmed about 4 times total, mainly be enticers since I fought a lot of those. So even if you had 170 mr, the higher level sirens would be a challenge.<br>
<br>
Overall though, these were not as bad as I thought, and soloable.   I wouldn't try to solo them pre-51 though. You need to be able to do full dmg, and you MUST have a quick casting high dmg spell like draught.  Only way I could get spells off was by catsing them before the siren finished casting theeirs, because if the siren hits you while you're casting and you don't completely resist it, it WILL interupt you.  <br>
<br>
Got two hairs after about 20 sirens. Both off of enticers.<br>
<br>
Good luck!<br>
